<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="borrow-v">borrow <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'bɒrəʊ/    美 /'bɑːroʊ/  </p>
<p>vt &amp; vi</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-lend">1.★ <strong>借；借用【 反：lend】</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>How many books can I borrow at a time?
我一次能借几本书？</p><footer>2015 北京</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don't like to borrow (money) <strong>from</strong> my friends<strong>borrowed</strong>
我不喜欢向朋友借钱。</p></div>

<h3 id="lend-borrow">辨析 lend, borrow</h3>
<p><strong>二者都译为“借”，但意义不同。</strong> </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You mustn't <strong>lend</strong> the book <strong>to</strong> others.
不许你把这本书借给别人。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He decided to <strong>borrow</strong> some money <strong>from</strong> the bank.
他决定到银行贷点款。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>引用；借用（思想、文字等）：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>English has <strong>borrowed</strong> many words <strong>from</strong> French.
英语借用了许多法语单词。</p></div></div>